race.comment: BOMBAY BOOM (2) has raced well in metro Open 2s and resumed with a dominant Maiden win at Albury. Led in that and may do the same here. Has a low gate and Heywood stays aboard the promising Matt Dale-trained galloper. He has plenty to give and can take the next step. MARGIN CALL (3) has claims building on his 1.6L defeat at Scone. In an elite stable, and is sure to keep improving. OUR LITTLE STAR (5) resumed here in stronger form and was a run short. Had switched to the Nick Olive yard and has decent metro and provincial form. Sharp improvement is on the cards. WONDERFUL MISTAKE (11) has a wide gate but was backed off the map winning a Gundagai Maiden first-up, and she is still shy of her best. Worth a look, briefly freshened.
